      "content": "While some argue that substantive due process stretches the Constitution, it's a vital tool for protecting our rights. Critics say it goes beyond what the Constitution explicitly states, but it's necessary to ensure that our government doesn't infringe on our fundamental freedoms. They prefer procedural due process, which focuses on fair procedures, but substantive due process goes further, safeguarding our most important rights from government overreach. It's a necessary check on power, ensuring that our liberties aren't just protected by the letter of the law, but by its spirit as well.",
      "source": "target",
