    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. So, basically, are you saying that the procedural due process argument is just a technicality used to avoid protecting actual human rights? It feels like the 'critics' you mentioned are just trying to find loopholes to undermine progress. Is there any real weight to their legal argument, or is it just a way to block civil rights advancements?",
